The TOI-1235 Exoplanetary System


Overview

TOI-1235 is a star with 0.64 times the mass of the Sun, and 0.63 times its radius. It is located 129.27 light years away from the solar system.

TOI-1235 is known to have 1 exoplanets in orbit around it.


Exoplanets in the TOI-1235 system


TOI-1235 b

TOI-1235 b was discovered by the Transiting Exoplanet Survey Satellite (TESS) observatory, in 2020-07, using the transit method. Its semi-major axis is 0.04 astronomical units, as compared to Earth's which is 1 astronomical unit. The mass of TOI-1235 b is 6.913 times the mass of Earth. The radius of TOI-1235 b is 1.738 that of Earth. At more than 10 Earth masses, TOI-1235 b is an ice giant, a planet that is made up mostly of volatiles like water, amonia and methane, and enveloped by a dense hydrogen and helium atmosphere, much like Uranus and Neptune in our solar system.
